rComments: This guy really just wants his students to learn and do well. Amazing lectures. Attend them even if you think you understand the course just to get some laughs from his hilarious teaching style and interesting life advice. 10/10 recommend

Professor Mathai is vigorous. He doesn't allow the use of books. He floods us with labs that are way beyond the level of people who haven't had a moderate experience in coding. He also has no apparent criteria on how he grades the tests or what percentage from the overall grade are his labs. In class, it's difficult to keep up if you're new
humor/confident/arrogant. He has great values and ideas in his mind, but sometimes he is not aware that students take time to understand them. I learned a lot from his class.
